<h1 style="margin-bottom:0px;">Database (Amazon RDS)</h1><div class="f14 metric" style="color:#656668;display:flex;"><img src="/assets/images/calendar.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="updateDate">&nbsp; Updated on 26/06/2019</span> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <img src="/assets/images/updated.png" style="height:12px;margin-top:auto;margin-bottom:auto;"><span class="readTime">&nbsp; 3 minutes to read</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div><br><div class="mw-parser-output"><p>Amazon RDS is a web service that makes it easier to set up, operate, and scale a relational database in the AWS cloud. It provides cost-efficient, resizable capacity for an industry-standard relational database and manages common database administration tasks.
<br>
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Create_and_configure_RDS">Create and configure RDS</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DataOpsB&amp;veaction=edit&amp;section=1" class="mw-editsection-visualeditor" title="Edit section: Create and configure RDS">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-divider"> | </span><a href="/mediawiki/index.php?title=Operations_Bridge:2019.05/DataOpsB&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Create and configure RDS">edit source</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<ol><li>Create a <b>Security Group</b> used to control access to database at: <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://console.aws.amazon.com/ec2/v2/home#SecurityGroups">https://console.aws.amazon.com/ec2/v2/home#SecurityGroups</a>.<br>It should include rules that resemble the following:<br><br><a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="OpsBridge2019.02Postgres1.jpg" src="/mediawiki/images/5/55/OpsBridge2019.02Postgres1.jpg" width="710" height="346" data-file-width="710" data-file-height="346"></a><br>
<ul><li>Select <b>VPC</b> created in section <a href="./itom/SMAX:2019.02/CreateVpcInstance" title="SMAX:2019.02/CreateVpcInstance">VPC preparation</a>.</li>
<li>Replace <b>Source</b> with your <b>VPC CIDR</b>.</li></ul></li>
<li>Create a <b>Subnet Group</b> at <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://console.aws.amazon.com/rds/home#db-subnet-groups">https://console.aws.amazon.com/rds/home#db-subnet-groups</a>.<br> It should include the private subnets where RDS instances will be launched.<br><br><a onclick="javascript:loadingImage(this);" class="image"><img alt="sma 1805 aws rds 2.png" src="/mediawiki/images/thumb/b/bc/sma_1805_aws_rds_2.png/650px-sma_1805_aws_rds_2.png" width="650" height="388" srcset="/mediawiki/images/b/bc/sma_1805_aws_rds_2.png 1.5x" data-file-width="813" data-file-height="485"></a><br>
<ul><li>Select <b>VPC</b> created in section <a href="./itom/SMAX:2019.02/CreateVpcInstance" title="SMAX:2019.02/CreateVpcInstance">VPC preparation</a>.<br></li>
<li>Select <b>Availability Zone</b>.</li>
<li>Select <b>private subnets</b>.<br><br><div class="Admonition_Note"><span class="autonumber">Note </span> You can use the private subnets prepared in section <a href="./itom/SMAX:2019.02/CreateExtraSubnets" title="SMAX:2019.02/CreateExtraSubnets">Subnet Preparation</a>. If you want to isolate database service, you can create more extra private subnets. </div></li></ul></li>
<li>Create a <b>DB instance</b> at <a target="1" rel="nofollow" class="external free" href="https://console.aws.amazon.com/rds/home">https://console.aws.amazon.com/rds/home</a>.
<ol><li>On the <b>Select engine</b> page, choose <b>Postgres</b>, and then click <b>Next</b>. For more supported RDS engines, see Support matrix.</li>
<li>On the Production page, select <b>Production</b> or <b>Dev/Test</b>, depending on whether you will use the database instance in a production or test environment, and then click <b>Next Step</b>.</li>
<li>On the <b>Specify DB Details</b> page, fill the fields with the information in the table below, and then click <b>Next Step</b>.<br></li></ol></li></ol>
<dl><dd><dl><dd><dl><dd><dl><dd><dl><dd><a class="buttonfullscr" onclick="javascript:loadingTableButton(this);"><button class="flscrbtn"><i class="material-icons flscricn">open_in_new</i><div style="margin: auto 5px;">View Fullscreen</div></button></a><table class="confluenceTable tablesorter">

